# ==============================================================================
# TEAM DEFINITIONS AND CONTACTS
# ==============================================================================

# Teams are defined in GitHub Organizations with the following structure:
#
# @executive-team - Executive leadership, strategic decisions
# @architecture-board - Senior architects, technical standards
# @security-team - Security engineers, compliance specialists
# @docs-team - Technical writers, documentation specialists
# @mcp-team - MCP developers, AI integration specialists
# @frontend-team - Frontend developers, UI/UX specialists
# @backend-team - Backend developers, API specialists
# @devops-team - DevOps engineers, infrastructure specialists
# @ai-team - AI/ML engineers, automation specialists
# @qa-team - QA engineers, testing specialists
# @data-team - Data engineers, analytics specialists
# @sre-team - SRE engineers, reliability specialists
# @integration-team - Integration specialists, third-party systems
# @payments-team - Payment processing specialists
# @database-team - Database administrators, data architects
# @design-system-team - Design system engineers, component specialists
# @technical-writers - Technical content creators
# @domain-experts - Subject matter experts by domain
# @tutorials-team - Tutorial content specialists
# @how-to-team - How-to guide specialists
# @reference-team - Reference documentation specialists
# @explanation-team - Explanation content specialists
# @anthropic-experts - Anthropic AI platform specialists
# @client-success-team - Client success managers, support specialists
# @solutions-team - Solutions architects, implementation specialists
# @compliance-team - Compliance officers, legal specialists
# @product-team - Product managers, business analysts
# @admin-team - Admin dashboard specialists
# @portal-team - Portal application specialists
# @trevorlam - Repository owner, final escalation point
#
# For team membership and contact information, see:
# - .github/teams/ directory
# - docs/guides/contributing/team-structure.md
# - Internal company directory
#
# ==============================================================================
# GOVERNANCE AND ESCALATION
# ==============================================================================
#
# 1. First-level approval: Pattern-matched team
# 2. Second-level escalation: Domain expert team
# 3. Third-level escalation: Architecture board
# 4. Final escalation: Executive team (@trevorlam)
#
# For security issues: Always escalate to @security-team immediately
# For incidents: Escalate to @sre-team and @executive-team
# For compliance: Escalate to @compliance-team and @executive-team
#
# ==============================================================================
# MAINTENANCE AND UPDATES
# ==============================================================================
#
# This file should be reviewed quarterly by:
# - @architecture-board (technical accuracy)
# - @docs-team (documentation clarity)
# - @executive-team (strategic alignment)
#
# Updates require:
# 1. PR with clear rationale
# 2. Approval from @architecture-board
# 3. Notification to affected teams
# 4. Documentation update in docs/CODEOWNERS.md
#
# Last reviewed: 2026-02-26
# Next review: 2026-05-26
